headline.main: Executives' Health; Physicians at Parley Urge Check-Ups And Taking Advice of Satchel Paige

byline.original: By HOWARD A. RUSK, M.D. MIAMI BEACH, FLA

docs.lead_paragraph: At the annual meeting of the American College of Physicians here this past week, Dr. James P. Baker opened a discussion on executive health with an anecdate: When speaking on the same subject a few months ago, Dr. Baker was asked, "Do men who have regular health examinations live longer and enjoy better health than those who don't?"
